  "notes": [
    "Prognostic mass state (t, qv, qc, qr, qi, qs, qg, qh) and surface precip (rain/snow/graupel/hail) are gated against the CANONICAL fp32 WRF oracle.",
    "WDM7 = WDM6 double-moment warm rain (Nc/Nr/Nn) + a SEPARATE precipitating single-moment HAIL class (qh, NO hail number Nh). The hail process terms (phaci/phacw/phacr/phacs/phacg, phaut graupel->hail, phmlt/pheml, phdep, phevp, pgwet/phwet wet growth) and the 4th semi-Lagrangian fall channel are exercised by cases 2/3/4/5 (case 4 grows surface hail; HAILNCV>0).",
    "Number concentrations (Nn=CCN, Nc=cloud, Nr=rain) are the double-moment additions; gated against the fp32 oracle with a slightly looser relative tolerance (cube-root lamda inversions + 1e1..1e10 dynamic range), with a PREDECLARED fp64 floor-dust fallback (a number field passes if it matches EITHER the fp32 OR the machine-precision fp64 oracle): the classic fp32 scheme leaves single-precision leftovers (~1e3 /kg) at fully-converted cells where the fp64 reference and the fp64 JAX port both correctly give 0 (case 4 k=8 Nr: fp32=1648, fp64=0, JAX=9e-13). The vs_fp64 column shows the port matches the fp64 truth to ~1e-6, confirming the residual is the fp32 REFERENCE's truncation, not a port error -- the SAME floor-dust handling WSM7/WDM6 apply to their categorical fields.",
    "Effective radii are diagnostic-only with categorical floors; gated vs the fp64 oracle, vs-fp32 recorded for transparency.",
    "Tolerances are identical to WDM6's: WDM7 adds only a single-moment hail mass class on top of the same double-moment number machinery + PLM sedimentation, so the fp32-vs-fp64 roundoff drivers (hence the principled bound) are the same."
